<p>
	<label for="settings_chyme_url">Chyme URL</label>
	<input type="text" id="settings_chyme_url" size=80 value="<%= settings['chyme_url'] %>" name="settings[chyme_url]" />
</p>

<p>
	Generate an "Incoming WebHook" URL from the Solution/Webhook configuration page on Chyme.  Copy/Paste the URL here remvoing any trailing slash. This URL can be changed on a per-project basis by creating a <a href="/custom_fields/new?type=ProjectCustomField">project custom field</a> named "Chyme URL" (without quotes).
</p>

<p>
	<label for="settings_assistant">Chyme Assistant</label>
	<input type="text" id="settings_assistant" value="<%= settings['assistant'] %>" name="settings[assistant]" />
</p>

<p>
	The assistant can be changed on a per-project basis by creating a
	<a href="/custom_fields/new?type=ProjectCustomField">project custom field</a> named "Chyme Assistant" (without quotes).
</p>

<p>
	<label for="settings_channel">Chyme Channel</label>
	<input type="text" id="settings_channel" value="<%= settings['channel'] %>" name="settings[channel]" />
</p>

<p>
	To disable notifications set to -.  The channel can be changed on a per-project basis by creating a
	<a href="/custom_fields/new?type=ProjectCustomField">project custom field</a> named "Chyme Channel" (without quotes).
</p>

<p>
	<label for="settings_post_updates">Post Issue Updates?</label>
	<input type="checkbox" id="settings_post_updates" value="1" name="settings[post_updates]" <%= settings['post_updates'] == '1' ? 'checked="checked"' : '' %> />
</p>
